  <br><b>General Recruiting Policy</b>
  <br><p>Fury's Edge is a guild which is entirely committed to conquering all of the most difficult challenges Everquest 
  has to offer. We often raid 5-6 days per week in order to see that we achieve our goals. The reward is often 
  self-fullfillment, or sometimes, just a learning experience. If you feel that you can commit the time and effort to help 
  the guild progress as a whole, then we may have a place for you in Fury's Edge.</p> 
  <br><b>Cross Server Applications</b>
  <br><p>Cross Server Applications are welcome, however; You must be 65 with at least 80AA points, as well as being a 
  class which is currently in demand. You'll need to send the recruiting officer a tell in game or an email to setup a time 
  for us to meet with you on your home server.</p>
  <br><b>Technical Requirements</b>
  <br><ul>
      <li>You absolutely must have a stable connection, we have no use for anyone who LD's frequently or lags constantly.</li>
	  <li>You need to have a PC capable of handling 50 people in tight spaces. What is playable is your call, but we can't 
	  have people unable to function due to poor machines.</li>
	  </ul>
  <br><p align="center"><b>IMPORTANT</b></p>
  <br><p>If you are online, raid attendance is MANDATORY. We often raid 6 days per week. Weekday raids usually begin at 
  7pm eastern time and can last anywhere from a few hours to past midnight. On weekends, we begin at 2pm eastern and raid 
  through the day(and night). <b>If you cannot dedicate yourself to raiding on this schedule, please do not apply.</b> Time zone 
  is an issue for some people, keep in mind we raid on Eastern Standard Time.</p>
  <br><p align="center"><b>DO NOT APPLY IF YOU CANNOT COMMIT TO RAIDING ON EST</b></p>
  <br><p>Fury's Edge is not for everyone, we are not a close knit family type of guild which you may find elsewhere. 
  We are a group of people completely dedicated to conquering everything that EQ has to offer. If you feel that you want to 
  dedicate your time and skill to our guild, start by sending the recruiting officer a tell in game. Once you're given the 
  go-ahead, please follow the link below to the Online Application Form.</p>
  <br><p align="center"><a href="appform.cfm">Online Application Form</a></p>
  <br><p>Once your Online Application is recieved and you are given the go-ahead to begin your application, please proceed to
  <a href="create_character1.cfm">this link</a> and create your profile with our website.
  Your profile will be used mainly to track your raid attendance and DKP statistics.</p>
